  <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#"/>

  <!-- owl:Class declarations -->

<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#WaterDistributionInfrastructure">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A water distribution infrastructure system, composed of various assets.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Water Distribution Infrastructure</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class WaterDistributionInfrastructure: Required by CQ01 to represent the infrastructure that composes assets.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class WaterDistributionInfrastructure: Required by CQ01 to represent the infrastructure that composes assets.: Initial creation
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Added subclass axiom to Asset to clarify that infrastructure is a type of asset.: To maintain consistency and align with the property 'composes' which has domain WaterDistributionInfrastructure and range Asset, suggesting infrastructure is an asset.
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class WaterDistributionInfrastructure: Required by CQ01 to represent the infrastructure that composes assets.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added subclass axiom to Asset to clarify that infrastructure is a type of asset.: To maintain consistency and align with the property 'composes' which has domain WaterDistributionInfrastructure and range Asset, suggesting infrastructure is an asset.
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added disjointness axiom with Device class.: To address missing disjoint axioms pitfall; infrastructure and devices are distinct types of assets.</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ01: Which assets compose a water distribution infrastructure?</dc:source>
  <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Asset'/>
<owl:disjointWith rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Device'/>
</owl:Class>

<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Asset">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A physical or logical component that is part of a water distribution infrastructure.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Asset</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class Asset: Required by CQ01 as components of infrastructure.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class Asset: Required by CQ01 as components of infrastructure.: Initial creation
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Removed incorrect subclass axiom to Thing (using local URI) because Thing is a built-in OWL class and the axiom is redundant.: To avoid confusion and incorrect referencing; every class is implicitly a subclass of owl:Thing.
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class Asset: Required by CQ01 as components of infrastructure.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Removed incorrect subclass axiom to Thing (using local URI) because Thing is a built-in OWL class and the axiom is redundant.: To avoid confusion and incorrect referencing; every class is implicitly a subclass of owl:Thing.</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ01: Which assets compose a water distribution infrastructure?</dc:source>
</owl:Class>

<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Device">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A device that is part of the water infrastructure, such as sensors, actuators, or water meters.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Device</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class Device: General class for devices in water infrastructure, from which Sensor, Actuator, WaterMeter specialize.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class Device: General class for devices in water infrastructure, from which Sensor, Actuator, WaterMeter specialize.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class Device: General class for devices in water infrastructure, from which Sensor, Actuator, WaterMeter specialize.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added disjointness axiom with WaterDistributionInfrastructure class.: To address missing disjoint axioms pitfall; devices and infrastructure are distinct types of assets.</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ04: Which types of sensors are used in water infrastructures?
    (competency_question) CQ05: Which types of actuators are used in water infrastructures?
    (competency_question) CQ06: A water meter is a device that measures different aspects of a water infrastructure.</dc:source>
  <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Asset'/>
<owl:disjointWith rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#WaterDistributionInfrastructure'/>
</owl:Class>

<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Sensor">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A device that senses or measures some property of water or the infrastructure.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Sensor</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class Sensor: Required by CQ04 to represent types of sensors.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class Sensor: Required by CQ04 to represent types of sensors.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class Sensor: Required by CQ04 to represent types of sensors.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added disjointness axioms with Actuator and WaterMeter classes.: To address missing disjoint axioms pitfall; sensor, actuator, and water meter are mutually exclusive device types.</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ04: Which types of sensors are used in water infrastructures?</dc:source>
  <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Device'/>
<owl:disjointWith rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Actuator'/>
<owl:disjointWith rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#WaterMeter'/>
</owl:Class>

<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Actuator">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A device that acts upon the water infrastructure, e.g., valves, pumps.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Actuator</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class Actuator: Required by CQ05 to represent types of actuators.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class Actuator: Required by CQ05 to represent types of actuators.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class Actuator: Required by CQ05 to represent types of actuators.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added disjointness axioms with Sensor and WaterMeter classes.: To address missing disjoint axioms pitfall; actuator, sensor, and water meter are mutually exclusive device types.</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ05: Which types of actuators are used in water infrastructures?</dc:source>
  <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Device'/>
<owl:disjointWith rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Sensor'/>
<owl:disjointWith rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#WaterMeter'/>
</owl:Class>

<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#WaterMeter">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A device that measures different aspects of a water infrastructure, such as flow, volume.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Water Meter</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class WaterMeter: Required by CQ06 and many subsequent questions about water meter properties.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class WaterMeter: Required by CQ06 and many subsequent questions about water meter properties.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class WaterMeter: Required by CQ06 and many subsequent questions about water meter properties.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added disjointness axioms with Sensor and Actuator classes.: To address missing disjoint axioms pitfall; water meter, sensor, and actuator are mutually exclusive device types.</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ06: A water meter is a device that measures different aspects of a water infrastructure.</dc:source>
  <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Device'/>
<owl:disjointWith rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Sensor'/>
<owl:disjointWith rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Actuator'/>
</owl:Class>

<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#WaterProperty">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A property of water, either physical or chemical.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Water Property</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class WaterProperty: Required by CQ33 and CQ34 to represent physical and chemical properties of water.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class WaterProperty: Required by CQ33 and CQ34 to represent physical and chemical properties of water.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class WaterProperty: Required by CQ33 and CQ34 to represent physical and chemical properties of water.: Initial creation</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ33: What are the physical properties of water?
    (competency_question) CQ34: What are the chemical properties of water?</dc:source>
</owl:Class>

<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#PhysicalProperty">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A physical property of water, e.g., temperature, pressure, turbidity.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Physical Property</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class PhysicalProperty: Required by CQ33 to represent physical properties.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class PhysicalProperty: Required by CQ33 to represent physical properties.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class PhysicalProperty: Required by CQ33 to represent physical properties.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added disjointness axiom with ChemicalProperty class.: To address missing disjoint axioms pitfall; physical and chemical properties are mutually exclusive categories.</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ33: What are the physical properties of water?</dc:source>
  <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#WaterProperty'/>
<owl:disjointWith rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#ChemicalProperty'/>
</owl:Class>

<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#ChemicalProperty">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A chemical property of water, e.g., pH, chlorine concentration.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Chemical Property</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class ChemicalProperty: Required by CQ34 to represent chemical properties.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class ChemicalProperty: Required by CQ34 to represent chemical properties.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class ChemicalProperty: Required by CQ34 to represent chemical properties.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added disjointness axiom with PhysicalProperty class.: To address missing disjoint axioms pitfall; chemical and physical properties are mutually exclusive categories.</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ34: What are the chemical properties of water?</dc:source>
  <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#WaterProperty'/>
<owl:disjointWith rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#PhysicalProperty'/>
</owl:Class>

<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#WaterIndicator">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">An indicator defined for water quality or quantity, e.g., for a specific location like Burgos.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Water Indicator</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class WaterIndicator: Required by CQ37 to represent water indicators defined for Burgos.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class WaterIndicator: Required by CQ37 to represent water indicators defined for Burgos.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class WaterIndicator: Required by CQ37 to represent water indicators defined for Burgos.: Initial creation</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ37: Which water indicators are defined for Burgos?</dc:source>
</owl:Class>

<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Tariff">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A tariff applied to water usage, with start date, duration, period.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Tariff</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class Tariff: Required by CQ38, CQ39, CQ40 to represent tariff information.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class Tariff: Required by CQ38, CQ39, CQ40 to represent tariff information.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class Tariff: Required by CQ38, CQ39, CQ40 to represent tariff information.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added disjointness axiom with BillingInfo class.: To address missing disjoint axioms pitfall; tariff and billing information are distinct concepts.</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ38: What is the start date and time of the tariff in use in the water meter?
    (competency_question) CQ39: What is the duration of the current tariff of the water meter?
    (competency_question) CQ40: What is the tariff period of the water meter?</dc:source>
  <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#BillingInfo'/>
</owl:Class>

<owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#BillingInfo">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Billing information associated with a water meter, including billing date and period.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Billing Information</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Ontology Generation Agent] Created class BillingInfo: Required by CQ42 and CQ43 to represent billing details.
    [Logical Consistency Agent] Created class BillingInfo: Required by CQ42 and CQ43 to represent billing details.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Created class BillingInfo: Required by CQ42 and CQ43 to represent billing details.: Initial creation
    [Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added disjointness axiom with Tariff class.: To address missing disjoint axioms pitfall; billing information and tariff are distinct concepts.</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ42: What is the billing date of the water meter?
    (competency_question) CQ43: What is the billing date period of the water meter?</dc:source>
  <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource='http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#Tariff'/>
</owl:Class>

